SvelteKit’s **remote `form` functions** are already progressively enhanced: spreading the remote form props onto `<form>` outputs a normal `method`/`action` for no‑JS submissions, and when JS is available it submits without a full reload. You just define the `form` on the server and use `{...createPost}` in the component.  
Source: `content-sveltekit.md` lines 512–549.  

**Minimal example**

```js
// src/routes/posts/data.remote.js
import { form } from '$app/server';

export const createPost = form(async (data) => {
  const title = data.get('title');
  // save post...
});
```

```svelte
<!-- src/routes/posts/+page.svelte -->
<script>
  import { createPost } from './data.remote';
</script>

<form {...createPost}>
  <input name="title" />
  <button>Publish</button>
</form>
```

This works without JS (standard form submission) and becomes enhanced with JS (no full reload).  
Source: `content-sveltekit.md` lines 512–549.

